INSERT INTO `assay_monograph_hplc_area_method_single_component` (`id`, `assay_hplc_area_method_single_component_id`, `assignment_id`, `test_request_id`, `serial_number`, `monograph`) VALUES
(1, 1, 10, 50, 'WE23456R', '<p>THE BLAME GAME</p>\r\n<p>Someone said &lsquo;do not give me money, but give me a job&rsquo;. This shows high levels of practicality. Many people from different parts of the country are currently dying of hunger every year and the government is soliciting help both locally and internationally.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Recently a mother delivered a baby boy in Turkana, unfortunately the baby had to survive on cod liver oil instead of the mother&rsquo;s breast milk. This is because the mother had not eaten even after going through the delivery process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hunger strike in Kenya is widely spread in arid and semi-arid regions where agricultural practices can be reinforced through irrigation. The members of the community blame the government for lack of relief food whereas the government then blames foreign nations for not bringing their aids to Kenya.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ministry of agriculture is setting up facilities which include training of the local farmers on the best methods of farming so that the same story cannot be repeated in the coming years. This therefore will prevent paralysis of activities such as education since children at these regions are not able to attend school regularly due to lack of food.</p>\r\n<p>Some of the methods that can be integrated can be adopting alternative farming methods such as growing other crops that can grow in the arid regions e.g. growth of sunflower and other crops.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This should call upon the researchers from agricultural institutions to set up such projects in order to eradicate hunger in these regions.</p>');

