-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.399999618530273px;">analyte</em><span style="color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.399999618530273px;">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><em style="color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.399999618530273px;">titrand</em><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: -webkit-isolate; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif;"><a style="text-decoration: none; color: #0b0080; white-space: nowrap; background: none;" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titration#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup><span style="color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.399999618530273px;">&nbsp;to determine concentration. The volume of titrant reacted is called&nbsp;</span><em style="color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.399999618530273px;">titre</em><span style="color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.399999618530273px;">.</span></p>');

